      "chapterId": "chapter15",
      "type": "Term",
      "front": "Families in Freedom",
      "back": "To begin with, freedom meant escaping the numerous injustices of slavery—punishment by the lash, the separation of families, denial of access to education, the sexual exploitation of black women by their owners—and sharing in the rights and opportunities of American citizens.",
