      "chapterId": "chapter15",
      "type": "Person",
      "front": "Hiram Revels",
      "back": "Early black officeholder during Reconstruction. Hiram Revels, who had been born free in North Carolina, was educated in Illinois, and served as a chaplain in the wartime Union army, in 1870 became the first black senator in American history. Hiram Revels appears throughout \"What Is Freedom?\": Reconstruction as a major historical actor.",
