      "front": "Robert Smalls",
      "back": "Black Reconstruction politician and veteran. Among the most celebrated black officeholders was Robert Smalls, who had worked as a slave on the Charleston docks before the Civil War and who won national fame in 1862 by secretly guiding the Planter, a Confederate vessel, out of the harbor and delivering it to Union forces. Smalls became a powerful political leader on the South Carolina Sea Islands and was elected to five terms in Congress. Robert Smalls appears throughout \"What Is Freedom?\": Reconstruction as a major historical actor.",
